It's a day-by-day struggle to keep the family safe, and we have no relatives in Afghanistan to stay with in case of emergency. The English we learned through our training can only take us so far.

But it's a big step into a new life. It's also a new start for my family and me.

Editor's Note: Sarasad K. is now settled with her family in Parris Island, South Carolina. This is her story as told Senate Committee on Armed Services Chairman Carl Levin (D-Mich.) during a hearing on Afghanistan on March 29, 2011.

(Carl Levin is chairman of the Senate Committee on Armed Services.)

(Karen Pace is a political affairs specialist with the Center for Strategic and International Studies/Rolapp Communications.)
